{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2019/08/21/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Protein-protein Interaction Annotated Corpora</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bioc.sourceforge.net/BioC-BioGRID.html\">BioC-BioGRID</a> - <a href=\"https://academic.oup.com/database/article/doi/10.1093/database/baw147/2884890\">paper</a> - 120 full text articles annotated for PPI and genetic interactions. Used in the BioCreative V BioC task.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:53:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Annotated Text Data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/UCDenver-ccp/CRAFT\">CRAFT</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/UCDenver-ccp/CRAFT\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">52</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":52,\"repo\":\"UCDenver-ccp/CRAFT\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - <a href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-94-024-0881-2_53\">paper</a> - 67 full-text biomedical articles annotated in a variety of ways, including for concepts and coreferences. Now on version 3.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:38:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Feed Readers</h2><h4>Single-click/drag-n-drop upload</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://elixi.re\">elixire</a> - Simple yet advanced screenshot uploading and link shortening service. (<a href=\"https://gitlab.com/elixire/elixire\">Source Code</a>, <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/elixire/elixiremanager\">Clients</a>) <code>AGPL-3.0</code> <code>Python</code></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:33:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Note-taking and Editors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://docpht.org/\">DocPHT</a> - With DocPHT you can take notes and quickly document anything and without the use of any database. (<a href=\"https://demo.docpht.org/\">Demo</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/kenlog/docpht\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kenlog/docpht\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">96</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":96,\"repo\":\"kenlog/docpht\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) <code>MIT</code> <code>PHP</code></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:33:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Polls and Events</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://calagator.org/\">Calagator</a> - Event aggregator. (<a href=\"https://github.com/calagator/calagator\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/calagator/calagator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">387</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":387,\"repo\":\"calagator/calagator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) <code>MIT</code> <code>Ruby</code></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:33:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Polls and Events</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://primelife.ercim.eu/results/opensource/63-dudle\">dudle</a> - Online scheduling application. (<a href=\"https://dudle.inf.tu-dresden.de/\">Demo</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/kellerben/dudle\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kellerben/dudle\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">247</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":247,\"repo\":\"kellerben/dudle\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) <code>AGPL-3.0</code> <code>Ruby</code></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:33:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Ontologies and Controlled Vocabularies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/knowledge_sources/metathesaurus/index.html\">UMLS Metathesaurus</a> - <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC308795/\">paper</a> - Mappings between >3.8 million concepts, 14 million concept names, and >200 sources of biomedical vocabulary and identifiers. It's big. It may help to prepare a subset of the Metathesaurus with the <a href=\"https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/implementation_resources/metamorphosys/help.html\">MetamorphoSys installation tool</a> but we're still talking about ~30 Gb of disk space required for the 2019 release. <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK9684/\">See the manual here</a>. Requires UTS account.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:30:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Code Libraries</h2><h3>Repos for Specific Datasets</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MIT-LCP/mimic-code\">mimic-code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MIT-LCP/mimic-code\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1272,\"repo\":\"MIT-LCP/mimic-code\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Code associated with the MIMIC-III dataset (see below). Includes some helpful <a href=\"https://github.com/MIT-LCP/mimic-code/tree/master/tutorials\">tutorials</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:22:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Biomedical Text Sources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://davis.wpi.edu/xmdv/datasets/ohsumed.html\">OHSUMED</a> - <a href=\"https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=188557\">paper</a> - 348,566 MEDLINE entries (title and sometimes abstract) from between 1987 and 1991. Includes MeSH labels. Primarily of historical significance.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T23:01:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Ontologies and Controlled Vocabularies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm/index.html\">RxNorm</a> - <a href=\"https://academic.oup.com/jamia/article/18/4/441/734170\">paper</a> - Normalized names for clinical drugs and drug packs, with combined ingredients, strengths, and form, and assigned types from the Semantic Network (see below). Released monthly.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T22:43:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Ontologies and Controlled Vocabularies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://semanticnetwork.nlm.nih.gov/\">UMLS Semantic Network</a> - <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2447396/\">paper</a> - Lists of 133 semantic types and 54 semantic relationships covering biomedical concepts and vocabulary. Is the Metathesaurus too complex for your needs? Try this. Does not require UTS account to download.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T22:43:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Annotated Text Data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wsd.nlm.nih.gov/\">Word Sense Disambiguation (WSD)</a> - <a href=\"https://bmcbioinformatics.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1471-2105-12-223\">paper</a> - 203 ambiguous words and 37,888 automatically extracted instances of their use in biomedical research publications. Requires UTS account.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T22:26:30.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rayokota/awesome-hbase","categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects</h2><h4>Graph</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vesoft-inc/nebula\">NebulaGraph</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vesoft-inc/nebula\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6163,\"repo\":\"vesoft-inc/nebula\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A high performance distributed Graph database.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T21:21:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Protein-protein Interaction Annotated Corpora</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://corpora.informatik.hu-berlin.de/corpora/brat2bioc/bioinfer_bioc.xml.zip\">BioInfer</a> - <a href=\"https://bmcbioinformatics.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1471-2105-8-50\">paper</a> - 1,100 sentences from biomedical research abstracts annotated for relationships (including PPI), named entities, and syntactic dependencies. <a href=\"http://mars.cs.utu.fi/BioInfer/\">Additional information and download links are here.</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T21:02:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Protein-protein Interaction Annotated Corpora</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://corpora.informatik.hu-berlin.de/corpora/brat2bioc/iepa_bioc.xml.zip\">IEPA</a> - <a href=\"http://psb.stanford.edu/psb-online/proceedings/psb02/abstracts/p326.html\">paper</a> - 486 sentences from biomedical research abstracts annotated for pairs of co-occurring chemicals, including proteins (hence, PPI annotations).</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T21:02:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Protein-protein Interaction Annotated Corpora</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://corpora.informatik.hu-berlin.de/corpora/brat2bioc/lll_bioc.xml.zip\">LLL</a> - <a href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Learning-Language-in-Logic-Genic-Interaction-Nedellec/0863a9d71955341b7e1a6a6877d44d4f0bb22671\">paper</a> - 77 sentences from research articles about the bacterium <em>Bacillus subtilis</em>, annotated for protein–gene interactions (so, fairly close to PPI annotations). <a href=\"http://genome.jouy.inra.fr/texte/LLLchallenge/#task1\">Additional information is here.</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T21:02:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"caufieldjh/awesome-bioie","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h3>Protein-protein Interaction Annotated Corpora</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://corpora.informatik.hu-berlin.de/corpora/brat2bioc/aimed_bioc.xml.zip\">AIMed</a> - <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15811782\">paper</a> - 225 MEDLINE abstracts annotated for PPI.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T20:41:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"stoeffel/awesome-fp-js","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.manning.com/books/grokking-simplicity\">Grokking Simplicity</a> teaches functional programming from first principles. It uses JavaScript for all code examples and it uses real-world scenarios. By <a href=\"https://github.com/ericnormand\">Eric Normand</a> (2019)</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T17:29:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0kIvpOlieSNdIPZbn-mO15YIjRHY2wI9\">Playlist - Programando en Blazor</a> - [Spanish] Series of videos about Blazor.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-08-21T14:41:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins","categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mdarocha/zsh-windows-title/issues\">windows-title</a> - Dynamically updates terminal window title with current directory and the last command run.</li>","updatedAt":